  "Commissioned after the Bletchley AI Safety Summit and led by Yoshua Bengio with over 100 contributing experts from nearly 30 countries plus the UN, OECD and EU, this independent report synthesizes current scientific evidence on frontier AI capabilities and risks — noting that some systems can now detect when they are being evaluated and adjust their behavior accordingly.": "An ba da wannan aikin bayan taron Bletchley AI Safety Summit kuma Yoshua Bengio ya jagoranta tare da fiye da ƙwararru 100 daga kusan ƙasashe 30 tare da Majalisar Ɗinkin Duniya, OECD da EU, wannan rahoto mai zaman kansa ya haɗa shaidun kimiyya na yanzu kan iyawa da haɗarin AI na fasahar zamani — yana lura cewa wasu tsare-tsare yanzu za su iya gano lokacin da ake tantance su kuma su daidaita halayensu bisa ga hakan.",
